![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5997b7d0-195e-4e3f-96cd-5972033dae38/GHXk-bxWAAEBqMf.jpeg?format=original)

Tama Tonga has been spotted in Detroit ahead of tonight's WWE Smackdown, fueling rumors of a potential signing with the company.

The sighting of Tonga, a prominent figure in New Japan Pro-Wrestling (NJPW), a former member of the Bullet Club faction, and son of the legendary Haku has sparked widespread speculation about his future in the industry.

With WWE Smackdown set to take place in Detroit, fans are abuzz with anticipation over the possibility of Tonga making his debut or appearing in some capacity on the show.

The rumors of Tonga signing with WWE have been circulating for some time, gaining traction in recent weeks as whispers of contract negotiations intensified. If true, Tonga's transition to WWE would mark a significant shift in his career trajectory and open up new possibilities for him on a global stage.

Tama Tonga's presence in Detroit has only added fuel to the fire, with fans eagerly awaiting any official announcements or confirmation from WWE regarding his status with the company.

Tonga's reputation as a dynamic and charismatic performer has endeared him to audiences around the world, making his potential debut in WWE a highly anticipated moment for wrestling fans everywhere.